==English==

To be sensual. 
Use of the senses.
In most common use this is an aspect of the lovers' relationship, not necessarily to be confused with sexual. Frequently they are combined. 
This is where theory comes into play. To be sensual with one's lover is generally considered to be affectionate in such a way the uses the sense of touch infused with the illusory quality of love. Passing energy through caress, rather than to use up. 
To adore, with touch.
